<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-24T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-24T01:00:00-05:00" n="518" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9660: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-24T14:00:00+08:00">August 24, 1937—2
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>547. In an interview granted today to Reuters aboard Japanese
                                flagship, Admiral Hasegawa made the following statement which the
                                Japanese Consul General confirms: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“It has been the intention of the Japanese Government to
                                        localize the Sino-Japanese conflict and to bring about
                                        ultimately closer and better relations with China. However,
                                        with the situation aggravated by Chinese to such an extent
                                        as it is, we deem it important that a safety zone should be
                                        established in and around Shanghai, and that all causes of
                                        further trouble should be removed once and for all.”</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>